<i>Braving the low 50s</i>
<i>Virginia winter</i>

14:28.852 --> 14:31.618
<i>and nursing a slight hangover,</i>

14:31.620 --> 14:33.921
<i>Cleveland Brown set out to win</i>

14:33.923 --> 14:37.391
<i>the Battle of Stoolbend</i>
<i>reenactment</i>

14:37.393 --> 14:40.294
<i>for the North.</i>

14:40.296 --> 14:44.065
CLEVELAND:
<i>Dear Donna,</i>
<i>I go to battle today</i>

14:44.067 --> 14:47.201
<i>and lest I should not be able</i>
<i>to call or text,</i>

14:47.203 --> 14:51.005
<i>I feel I must needs</i>
<i>write to you.</i>

14:51.007 --> 14:53.174
<i>Oh, Donna, my love.</i>

14:53.176 --> 14:55.910
<i>How I miss the warmth</i>
<i>of your arms,</i>

14:55.912 --> 14:57.945
<i>the taste of your lips,</i>

14:57.947 --> 15:01.949
<i>the caress of your soft hand</i>
<i>on my under-satchel.</i>

15:01.951 --> 15:04.986
<i>Yours eternally, Cleveland.</i>

15:04.988 --> 15:09.556
TIM:
<i>Dearest Arianna, I fear</i>
<i>I may not make it home</i>

15:09.558 --> 15:12.826
<i>in time</i>
<i>for</i> So You Think You Can Dance.

15:12.828 --> 15:16.764
<i>Please make sure</i>
<i>the TiVo does not delete it.</i>

15:16.766 --> 15:19.166
HOLT:
<i>Dear Penthouse Forum,</i>

15:19.168 --> 15:22.503
<i>never thought these stories</i>
<i>were actually true till today.</i>

15:22.505 --> 15:24.505
<i>Dressed up like</i>
<i>a Civil War guy,</i>

15:24.507 --> 15:27.375
<i>nailed a chick with pinkeye</i>
<i>in a Taco Bell bathroom.</i>

15:27.377 --> 15:29.277
MAN:
Fire!

15:30.595 --> 15:32.096
[GUNSHOTS]

15:36.251 --> 15:38.502
[GROANING]

15:38.504 --> 15:40.338
Attack their right flank.

15:41.740 --> 15:43.140
[YELLING]

15:43.142 --> 15:45.759
There are a lot more bad guys
than I expected.

15:45.761 --> 15:48.929
How are we supposed
to fake win this fake battle?

15:48.931 --> 15:51.165
Who cares? Let's just tell
everyone we won.

15:51.167 --> 15:53.000
No. We have to fight.

15:53.002 --> 15:54.936
Oh, if there was only
some way to know

15:54.938 --> 15:56.204
what was about to happen

15:56.206 --> 16:00.241
in this reenactment of an actual
historic event-- Hello.

16:00.243 --> 16:03.794
Okay. Boring. All right.

16:03.796 --> 16:07.365
Boring. Useful. Boring.

16:07.367 --> 16:09.534
Word I don't know.
I'll skip it.

16:09.536 --> 16:12.336
Afraid to say it out loud
for fear of being judged.

16:12.338 --> 16:15.273
Oh, all right.
"Bay-ah-nets."

16:15.275 --> 16:17.608
No? Okay, we got
what we need to know.

16:17.610 --> 16:20.211
Let's go.

16:20.213 --> 16:21.479
TIM:
Bayonets.

16:23.065 --> 16:25.400
The Confederate battalion
is approaching.

16:25.402 --> 16:26.867
No time to dilly-dally.

16:26.869 --> 16:29.070
Over that ridge, you scalawags.

16:29.072 --> 16:30.371
Charge!

16:30.373 --> 16:33.274
Wait. No, no charge.

16:33.276 --> 16:35.576
We've got
the entire play-by-play

16:35.578 --> 16:37.979
of the Battle of Stoolbend
right here.

16:37.981 --> 16:41.615
If we go over that ridge,
it's a massacre.

16:41.617 --> 16:45.219
No doi. We all know what
happens. This is a reenactment.

16:45.221 --> 16:47.088
Now,
just stick to the script.

16:47.090 --> 16:49.690
That's an order, lieutenant.

16:51.293 --> 16:53.760
Oh! You shot me.

16:53.762 --> 16:55.762
I'm mortally wounded.

16:55.764 --> 16:58.349
But you can't.
That's not what happened.

16:58.351 --> 17:03.103
Well, in the words of Raj,
it's what's happening now.

17:03.105 --> 17:04.722
[GROANS]

17:04.724 --> 17:05.957
ALL:
Hmm?

17:05.959 --> 17:06.824
Now, the rest of you,

17:06.826 --> 17:09.693
let's make history
our bitch.

17:09.695 --> 17:13.414
Any of you losers
wanna win for a change?

17:13.416 --> 17:14.232
ALL:
Hm?

17:14.234 --> 17:15.733
Will we still be done
by 4:30?

17:15.735 --> 17:18.068
Probably even sooner because
we're just gonna sneak up

17:18.070 --> 17:19.937
on everybody and kill them.

17:19.939 --> 17:20.872
Okay.
Sure.

17:20.874 --> 17:23.007
But I seriously need
to be done by 4:30.

17:23.009 --> 17:24.725
[♪]

17:36.571 --> 17:39.140
Hi, guys.

17:39.142 --> 17:41.508
Hey, that wasn't the way we--
The rules, Jeff.

17:41.510 --> 17:43.544
If you get shot,
you have to die.

17:43.546 --> 17:46.113
Yeah, do the rules say
anything about wearing Tevas?

17:46.115 --> 17:48.883
But we're going
to the lake after this.

17:48.885 --> 17:50.218
[BOTH GROAN]

17:50.220 --> 17:51.518
Yes.
Hot damn.

17:56.525 --> 17:59.994
HOLT:
Ha-ha. Die, Daddy.
Die, Daddy.

17:59.996 --> 18:02.630
Die, Daddy. Die, Daddy.

18:02.632 --> 18:05.799
[SOBBING]
Die, Daddy.

18:05.801 --> 18:07.635
That's a good--
Good job, Holt.

18:07.637 --> 18:10.738
Not, uh--
Not creeping me out at all.

18:11.657 --> 18:14.191
[GRUNTS]

18:14.193 --> 18:16.560
[WHINNIES]

18:18.797 --> 18:20.397
[SNORTING]

18:20.399 --> 18:22.500
[WHINNIES]

18:22.502 --> 18:25.503
Dial it back, buddy.
You already got the part.

18:27.439 --> 18:29.574
I think we got them all,
Cleveland.

18:29.576 --> 18:30.575
[GUNSHOT]

18:30.577 --> 18:31.909
Not quite.

18:31.911 --> 18:33.594
Oh, crap.

18:33.596 --> 18:35.930
Okay, here we go.

18:39.134 --> 18:42.487
I heard five pretend bullets
come out of that gun.

18:42.489 --> 18:44.789
You got one bullet left.

18:44.791 --> 18:46.624
I only need one.

18:46.626 --> 18:48.559
[♪]

18:52.381 --> 18:54.348
Damn, I missed.
Terrible shot.

18:54.350 --> 18:56.884
No reason I should've
missed you, but I did.

18:56.886 --> 18:58.602
[LAUGHS]

18:58.604 --> 19:02.440
You should've known
you can't change history.

19:03.925 --> 19:06.193
No!

19:07.296 --> 19:09.697
[GRUNTS]

19:09.699 --> 19:12.917
Lester, you took a pretend
bullet for me.

19:12.919 --> 19:14.118
But why?

19:14.120 --> 19:16.187
Turns out a lot
of the Confederates here

19:16.189 --> 19:18.155
are a bunch of rich dipsticks.

19:18.157 --> 19:21.592
I realized I got more in common
with poor people like you.

19:21.594 --> 19:23.594
Comfortably middle class,
but yeah.

19:23.596 --> 19:25.796
Yes, the blood I'm not shedding

19:25.798 --> 19:28.232
is in the name of loyalty
and friendship,

19:28.234 --> 19:32.302
which are more important
to me than any fake war.

19:32.304 --> 19:35.072
Okay, you can take my head
out of your lap now.

19:35.074 --> 19:36.340
Touching.

19:36.342 --> 19:38.476
Now die, Yankee.

19:40.345 --> 19:42.163
Got you.
No.

19:42.165 --> 19:44.465
Uh, you only got me
in the arm.

19:44.467 --> 19:47.335
Maybe so, but considering
the medical care of the time,

19:47.337 --> 19:50.371
you would've had it amputated
with nonsterile equipment,

19:50.373 --> 19:53.708
and later died
from a bacterial infection.

19:53.710 --> 19:56.694
You're right. You win.

19:58.063 --> 20:00.264
Hear ye, hear ye.

20:00.266 --> 20:05.302
I hereby declare victory
in the Battle of Stoolbend

20:05.304 --> 20:06.603
for the North.

20:06.605 --> 20:08.939
[ALL CHEERING]

20:08.941 --> 20:12.376
NARRATOR:
<i>The forces of tolerance</i>
<i>won a noble victory that day</i>

20:12.378 --> 20:14.178
<i>on the fields of Stoolbend.</i>

20:14.180 --> 20:15.896
<i>There was much revelry</i>

20:15.898 --> 20:18.599
<i>and many flagons</i>
<i>of the finest pale ale,</i>

20:18.601 --> 20:21.569
<i>as the victorious</i>
<i>Union Army toasted</i>

20:21.571 --> 20:24.972
<i>their triumphant</i>
<i>rewriting of history.</i>

20:24.974 --> 20:27.208
<i>[TIM GROWLING]</i>
<i>Things briefly got weird</i>

20:27.210 --> 20:31.245
<i>between Tim and Holt,</i>
<i>but they're cool now.</i>

20:31.247 --> 20:34.315
<i>And after all the bars</i>
<i>had stopped serving,</i>

20:34.317 --> 20:37.585
<i>they realized</i>
<i>the war was not yet won.</i>

20:37.587 --> 20:40.121
<i>So with the aid of Donna's car,</i>

20:40.123 --> 20:42.456
<i>they once</i>
<i>and for all dismantled</i>

20:42.458 --> 20:45.993
<i>the statue</i>
<i>of B. Emerson Plunkett.</i>

20:45.995 --> 20:47.861
ALL: <i>Yeah!</i>
<i>[CAR REVS, STATUE THUDS]</i>

20:47.863 --> 20:51.432
<i>Then they got fined by the city</i>
<i>and had to put it back up,</i>

20:51.434 --> 20:55.419
<i>where it still stands</i>
<i>proudly today.</i>

20:55.421 --> 20:58.889
<i>It is the South, after all.</i>

21:00.842 --> 21:02.810
[♪]

21:33.909 --> 21:36.844
[English - US - Line 21]
